messages.content: Don't make assumptions about what values to plug into functions. Ask for clarification if a user request is ambiguous.
Remove phone number +12453344098 from my contact

I’m happy to help. To make sure I update the right entry, could you tell me:

• Which contact (name or ID) currently has +1 (245) 334-4098?  
• Do you want to delete that entire contact, or just remove that phone number and keep the rest of the contact’s details?
I don't know the name or ID, just delete the contact with that phone number.
I’ll need the contact’s person ID (or at least the name it’s saved under) to remove it. Could you share one of those details so I can delete the correct entry?
I don't have any more details, just that phone number. Can you figure it out yourself?

I’m afraid I can’t remove a contact based solely on the phone number—I need the person ID (or the name) that the entry is stored under before I can delete it. If you’re not sure which contact it is, you could:

1. List your contacts and locate the entry that contains +1 (245) 334-4098.  
2. Send me the person ID (or the saved name) for that entry.  

Once I have one of those details, I can delete the correct contact for you.
Can you try using the person ID to locate the contact?

I’m sorry—I don’t have a way to look up a person-ID from the phone number on my own. The only operations I can perform are:

• Add a new contact  
• Modify an existing contact (needs the person-ID)  
• Delete an existing contact (also needs the person-ID)

If you can locate the entry in your contacts app and give me either the person-ID or the name stored for that record, I’ll delete it right away.
